  "prompt": "How do I re-apply for an H1B after cancelled without prejudice?",
  "response": "Here are steps to re-apply for an H1B after a cancellation without prejudice:\n\n1. Determine Cancellation Reason\n- Understand why the previous H1B was cancelled\n- Ensure there are no underlying issues preventing future applications\n\n2. Eligibility Assessment\n- Confirm you still meet H1B visa requirements\n- Check if you have remaining H1B quota eligibility\n- Verify you haven't exhausted maximum H1B petition opportunities\n\n3. Employment Requirements\n- Secure a new job offer from a qualifying employer\n- Ensure employer is willing to sponsor your H1B visa\n- Obtain a valid Labor Condition Application (LCA)\n\n4. Documentation Preparation\n- Gather updated professional documentation\n- Collect current educational certificates\n- Prepare detailed job description\n- Compile comprehensive work experience records\n\n5. Filing Process\n- Work with employer's immigration lawyer\n- Complete Form I-129\n- Submit all required supporting documents\n- Pay necessary filing fees\n- Consider premium processing if time-sensitive\n\n6. Potential Considerations\n- Consult immigration attorney for personalized guidance\n- Address any potential complications from previous cancellation\n- Be prepared to provide additional explanations if requested\n\nRecommended: Seek professional legal advice for specific situation assessment.",
